The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Tough task for Indian eves
                                                                                                                                                                                           Tough task for Indian eves
                      
	Kazan (Russia): With their fate for a berth in Beijing Olympics hanging in balance, India have their task cut out when they take on Belgium in the womens hockey Olympic qualifiers here on Tuesday.         
	The Indians started the tournament with a comfortable 3-1 victory over hosts Russia in their opening match but suffered a big setback in the second match when they went down 1-2 to Netherlands Antilles.         
	The Indians have no option but to win against Belgium to stay in contention for a spot in the Beijing Olympics. (PTI)                                                                                                                          
